title: Australia becomes first country to legalise medical psychedelics
description: Australia has become the first country to allow psychiatrists to prescribe psychedelics to patients with depression or post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD).

title: Telescope launches on mission to uncover secrets of dark universe
description: A European space telescope has been launched on a million-mile journey to map the dark universe.

title: YouTube bodybuilding star 'dies of aneurysm age 30'
description: A YouTube bodybuilding star known as Joesthetics has died at the age of 30, according to posts shared on social media by his friends and girlfriend.

title: Elon Musk applies temporary reading limits for all Twitter users with immediate effect
description: Twitter has applied temporary daily reading limits to address "extreme levels" of data scraping and system manipulation, Elon Musk has said.

title: 'Serious threat' remains at Zaporizhzhia nuclear plant, Zelenskyy warns
description: Volodymyr Zelenskyy has warned that the situation at the Zaporizhzhia nuclear plant in southern Ukraine remains a "serious threat".

title: Store owner fears teen's death being used by looters as 'pretext for robbing'
description: Franc Attali lost 100,000 euros (£86,000) in a night, his shop one of dozens in Marseille broken into by rioters.

title: 'One of our brightest talents': Tributes as driver, 18, killed in Belgium race crash
description: A teenage driver has died in a crash at a race in Belgium.

title: Dutch king apologises for country's historic involvement in slavery
description: King Willem-Alexander has apologised and asked for forgiveness over the Netherlands' historic involvement in slavery, describing it as "a crime against humanity".

title: Ukrainian football legend backs Olympic ban on Russian athletes
description: Andriy Shevchenko is more familiar representing Ukrainians as a sporting icon than any form of statesman.

title: Macron axes state visit to Germany amid protest unrest
description: President Emmanuel Macron has postponed a state visit to Germany due to the ongoing protests and riots across France.

title: Wagner boss will keep a low profile in Belarus - but he remains a dangerous animal
description: Following Yevgeny Prigozhin's abortive "march for justice" towards the Russian capital last weekend, President Lukashenko of Belarus intervened and apparently offered the Wagner boss safe sanctuary in exile.

title: 'I'll put a bullet in your head': Witness says French police threatened teen before fatal shooting
description: A young man who was in the car with the 17-year-old shot and killed by a police officer in France, sparking unrest across the country, has shared his story to "establish the truth".

title: At least 51 dead after truck crashes into market traders in Kenya
description: At least 51 people have died after a truck rammed into market traders and several other vehicles in western Kenya.

title: New advice issued for UK travellers to France
description: UK travellers to France have been warned to be aware of the ongoing riots after a 17-year-old was fatally shot by police.

title: Ex-Brazil president barred from running for office until 2030
description: Brazil's former president Jair Bolsonaro has been barred from public office until 2030 after a panel of judges concluded he abused power and cast unfounded doubts on the country's electronic voting system.

title: Another night of looting and lawlessness - and nobody knows what will happen next
description: On Pont Neuf, right in the very heart of Paris, a blend of people. Tourists, smart-dressed locals, and lots of police officers in riot gear.
